com.apstrata.client.android.connection
Interface Connection

All Known Implementing Classes:
AnonymousConnection, OwnerConnection, TokenConnection, UserConnection
public interface Connection

interface for connection implementations. the connection interface specifies methods for generating request signatures. request signatures are lists of name/value pairs that are appended as parameters to urls invoked by the apstrata android client. these parameters collectively form the request's signature and are used by server side code to validate the request. request signatures come in 2 flavours: complex and simple, hence the 2 corresponding methods of the interface.

getSimpleRequestSignature

java.util.List<org.apache.http.NameValuePair> getSimpleRequestSignature(java.lang.String action,
                                                                        java.util.List<org.apache.http.NameValuePair> parameters,
                                                                        java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.util.List<java.io.File>> files)
                                                                        throws java.lang.Exception
builds a simple request signature corresponding to the combination of the request's action, text parameters and file parameters (for file upload requests)

Parameters:
action: - the name of the apstrata endpoint invoked by the request, ie, SaveDocument, RunScript, etc...
parameters: - the list of request parameters, passed as name/value pairs
files: - the list of the request's file parameters
Returns:
the simple signature, consisting of a list of name/value parameters that should be included in the request
Throws:
java.lang.Exception
